<p>Amusingly nonsensical, but one thing kinda bugs me:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Instances of SCP-613 have been sporadically appearing around the world at a rate of once every 5 to 7 months. Operations are ongoing to investigate if there is any individual or organization actively producing or spreading SCP-613.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>How would we possibly know this? Through what means would the Foundation find out about these things existing? If I think my bread is talking to me, I'm damn well not going to spread that around. Plus, the Foundation has a very short time limit to find these things in before they're destroyed by consumption or by spoilage. How could they do it? Networks of millions of people across the world looking for anomalous bread?</p>
<p>Also, I want a note about how the bread tastes.</p>

